==Ancient Greek==

===Etymology===
From [[ἄρχω]] {{GG|757}} and [[Λαοδικεύς]] {{GG|2994}}; people ruling; 

===Pronunciation===
*Ἀρχέλαος / Archelaos / ar-khel'-ah-os

===Proper noun===
'''Ἀρχέλαος'''

# Archelaus, a Jewish king: - [[Archelaus]].

